	/**
	 * This method will initiate a query asynchronously using the Tanium API Gateway (APIGW).
	 *  It will wait only the specified number of seconds (the value of the maxWaitTime argument,
	 *  which is set to 5 (seconds) by default). After the specified number of seconds, whether
	 *  any machines have responded yet or not, the APIGW will return a response which will be
	 *  returned by this method.
	 * The returned object will be virtually identical to the response from the .getNextPage()
	 *  method. The value of the refresh cursor (located at data.endpoints.collectionInfo
	 *  .startCursor) will be stored in the current instance of the GatewayQueryUtil class, so
	 *  that .refreshQueryWithToken() can be called later to retrieve the results of the query
	 *  without having to store and pass around the refresh cursor. However, if you're "refreshing"
	 *  this query elsewhere (such as in a different step in a Flow), you will need to pass the
	 *  refresh cursor into the .refreshQueryWithToken() method in that new instance of the
	 *  GatewayQueryUtil class.
