	 *  used in conjunction with one another, in some kind of loop that waits until the response
	 *  meets some condition for completeness. For example, you might want to continue calling
	 *  .refreshQueryWithToken() until the value of data.endpoints.collectionInfo
	 *  .respondedPercentage is greater than 0.85 (85%), or until the value of data.endpoints
	 *  .edges.length is greater than 0 (meaning at least one machine has responded).
