	/**
	 * This method will initiate a truly asynchronous query using the configuration provided by
	 *  calling other methods of the GatewayQueryUtil class (such as .addSensor() and
	 *  .addFilter()). It will use .initQueryGetTokenAsync() and .refreshQueryWithToken() in the
	 *  background automatically, and only return a result when the query is complete (based on
	 *  the minimumEndpointCount or minimumResponsePercent arguments), or some maximum is reached
	 *  (such as maxRetries or maxWaitTimePerRequest).
	 *
	 * @param {number} [minimumEndpointCount=0] - The minimum number of endpoints that must be
	 *    returned by the query before the query will be considered complete, and the response will
	 *    be returned by this method. If this value is set to 0 (or unspecified), it will be
	 *    ignored.
